quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  70,40,"So I do swear by the Fosterer of the rising places/times and setting places/times (of the sun), that We are certainly able"
  70,41,to replace (them by others) better than them and We are not to be overcome
  70,42,"So leave them involved in idle talk and play, till they meet their day which they are promised"
  70,43,"The day they will come out from their graves in haste, as if rushing towards a goal"
  70,44,"(with) their eyes humbled, disgrace covering them, that is the day which they were promised"
  71,1,"We had sent Nuh to his people, (saying), “Warn your people before a painful punishment comes on them.”"
  71,2,"He said, “O my people ! I am a clear warner to you"
  71,3,that you should serve (worship) Allah and fear Him and obey me
  71,4,"He will (for give and) protect you from your sins and give you time till an appointed term. When the term of Allah comes (to an end), it will certainly not be postponed, had you but known.”"
  71,5,"He said, “My Fosterer! I invited my people (towards You) night and day"
  71,6,but my invitation did not increase in them anything except running away (from the truth)
  71,7,"And whenever I invited them that You will protectively forgive them, they put their fingers in their ears and covered, themselves with garments and persisted (in refusing) and considered themselves great (due to) pride"
  71,8,Then I invited them aloud
  71,9,then I invited them publicly and secretly in private
  71,10,"then I said: Seek protective forgiveness of your Fosterer, He is certainly Protectively Forgiving"